# Upload rules for `railway up`. When present, Railway uses this instead of
# .gitignore. Unlike .gitignore we DO upload public/data/* so the locally-built
# dataset ships as a bundled fallback — the Railway build environment can't
# always reach CelesTrak, and without a bundled dataset the site would deploy
# empty. Build the dataset locally (`npm run build:data`) before `railway up`.
node_modules
.git
dist
.vite
.env
.env.*
.DS_Store
*.log
*.tsbuildinfo
.design/
.railway/
docs/
